ENTRY            F1530   20251017   20260305   20260305       F106
SUBENT        F1530001   20251017   20260305   20260305       F106
BIB                 14         38
TITLE      Measurement of the 10B(d,n)11C reaction cross-section
           in the energy range of 0.05-0.57 MeV in inverse
           kinematics
AUTHOR     (P.S.Prusachenko,A.F.Gurbich,T.L.Bobrovsky,
           M.V.Bokhovko)
REFERENCE  (J,ARI,225,111999,2025)
           #doi:10.1016/j.apradiso.2025.111999
INSTITUTE  (4RUSFEI)
FACILITY   (ACCEL,4RUSFEI) IPPE 3-MV tandem accelerator
INC-SOURCE Boron ion beam from 0.6 to 3.2 MeV that corresponded
           to the energy range of deuterons for the reaction in
           direct kinematics from 0.05 to 0.57 MeV. The charge
           state of the boron ions was 2+ in the energy range of
           1.0-3.2 MeV and 1+ for energies of 0.6 and 0.8 MeV.
DETECTOR   (NAICR) Two scintillation detectors based on the
           150x100 mm NaI(Tl) crystals were used as gamma-ray
           detectors. Both detectors were located on the same
           axis with the target at angles of +-30 degr. relative
           to the beam axis.
METHOD     (COINC,BCINT)
ANALYSIS   (DECAY)
SAMPLE     A titanium layer saturated with deuterium atoms on a
           molybdenum backing was used as a target. The target
           diameter was 11 mm. The mean thickness of the target
           was 1.40+-0.06 mg/cm2 at the deuterium atom
           concentration of 56+-2%. The thickness of the carbon
           build-up on the target surface during the experiment
           was 28 mu-g/cm2.
ADD-RES    Comparison with data from TENDL-2023 was performed.
ERR-ANALYS Total systematic uncertainty is about 11%.
           (ERR-S) Statistical error
           (ERR-1) Beam current uncertainty
           (ERR-2) Efficiency uncertainty
           (ERR-3) Uncertainty associated with stopping power
           (ERR-4) Uncertainty of determination of deuterium
                   concentration
STATUS     (APRVD) Entry was approved by Dr. P.S. Prusachenko.
HISTORY    (20251017C)
ENDBIB              38
COMMON               4          3
ERR-1      ERR-2      ERR-3      ERR-4
